SIMPLE: redemise
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redemise
<hw>Re`de*mise"</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧`d⟦esl⟧*m⟦imac⟧z")</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <def>To demise back; to convey or transfer back, as an
estate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redemise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Redemise
<hw>Re`de*mise"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The transfer
of an estate back to the person who demised it; reconveyance; <as>as,
the demise and <ex>redemise</ex> of an estate</as>. See under
<er>Demise</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redemonstrate</ent>⟦br⟧
